The paper proposes a novel RNN architecture for language modeling tasks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of LSTM cells, which are commonly used in various AI applications, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed architecture on various language modeling tasks, which involves the use of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's experiments involve character-level language modeling, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) applications, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
